content: I have thumper on pc and it's honestly amazing. Thus I downloaded it on my phone too. I generally use Bluetooth in ear headphones. The problem is that when I'm using those headphones, thumper just kinda dies. The music is what i can only describe as choppy, as in its like after every note there's a pause, making the game impossible to play with sound and really not fun without. I love this game so I'm hoping, developers, that you fix that. I don't think the problem is on my end.
replyContent:
We use a "low latency" audio mode because low audio/video latency is needed (Android by default has bad latency). This mode can cause stuttering with bluetooth. But the bigger problem is that bluetooth also adds a lot more latency itself. 

We recommend speakers/wired 'phones. This is mentioned in the store description, so sorry if you missed that.

replyContent: We don't have calibration on any platform. You need BOTH low audio + video latency for the game. Calibration would add video latency to match audio latency, but that would result in sluggish controls. Your S8+ should be very capable of running it with low latency. We recommend turning off power saving, gestures, and avoiding bluetooth audio.
